        "content": " When, bhikkhus, a carpenter or a carpenterãs apprentice looks at the handle of his adze, he sees the impressions of his fingers and his thumb, but he does not know: ãSo much of the adze handle has been worn away today, so much yesterday, so much earlier.ã But when it has worn away, the knowledge occurs to him: it has worn away. Liberation happens naturally as the result of cultivating the Path. ",
