        "translator": "Bhante Sujato",
        "content": "The Jain leader Mahává¨ra, known as NigaÃ¿Ã¿Ùha Nátaputa in the Buddhist tradition, is visited by Citta the Householder. Mahává¨ra asks him whether he believes in a state of immersion free from thought. When Citta replies that he doesnãt, Mahává¨ra is (prematurely) delighted. Citta goes on to explain that he needs no faith because heãs already realized such a state himself in one of the most epic ãmic-dropsã of the Páli Canon. ",
